text: Ricardo Pietreczko (born 20 October 1994) is a German professional darts player. He reached the last 48 of the 2017 World Masters. He made his PDC European Tour debut in the 2018 International Darts Open, where he lost 6–4 to eventual quarter-finalist Ryan Searle. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:German darts players
